name: Pirropus Cytinus
description:
--Fig.11--
Pirroupus Cytinus is a Sciruidae Poale creature from Sancho, an exoplanet located 49.8 light years from Earth, orbiting the star Mu Arae.
Pirroupus lives in big oceans of liquid Arsenic, eating a polen-like food from huge Coral Flowers. As the species itself is part flower, they give back part of the polen they’ve eaten, with even more nutrients, to smaller creatures in their environment.
It has been said that Pirropus smells really good, and the oceans they live in have one of the sweetest scents in the universe, a mix of different alien-flowers.
